      "body" : "@DanielF &#39;s confusion is understandable because the comment in the answer is misleading. The 50  in <code>rand.nextInt(50)</code> will only give the maximum in this situation. <code>rand.nextInt(50)</code> will return an integer between 0 (inclusively) and 50 (exclusively) (in other words [0-49]). We add 1 to have [1-50]. So, if you take 45 as a minimum and add it to rand.nextInt(50), you&#39;ll have a value between 45 and 94 inclusively."
